WEBVTT

00:38.622 --> 00:40.248
ORIGINAL WORK TATSUKI FUJIMOTO

01:08.360 --> 01:10.196
<i>It's that same dream again.</i>

01:10.905 --> 01:14.241
<i>It's that same dream I always dream...
And always forget.</i>

01:22.208 --> 01:23.209
Denji.

01:25.711 --> 01:26.879
Pochita!

01:27.588 --> 01:29.340
Pochita, come out!

01:29.840 --> 01:32.217
We're just in a dream right now.
Let me pet you.

01:32.218 --> 01:33.468
Denji.

01:39.558 --> 01:41.226
Do not open the door. No matter what.

02:02.331 --> 02:04.749
What's going on? You're so loud.

02:06.961 --> 02:08.504
I had a bad dream.

02:18.138 --> 02:19.265
Am I still in a dream?

02:19.807 --> 02:21.266
What are you talking about?

02:27.773 --> 02:30.066
What's going on?

02:30.067 --> 02:33.319
Where did I get all this power?

02:33.320 --> 02:37.032
So this isn't a dream.

02:58.554 --> 02:59.555
CHAINSAW MAN

03:06.145 --> 03:07.855
PUBLIC SAFETY DEVIL HUNTERS
LARGE-SCALE ATTACK

04:34.942 --> 04:35.943
ONE MOMENT PLEASE.

05:06.724 --> 05:09.727
CHAINSAW MAN - THE MOVIE:
REZE ARC

05:12.563 --> 05:14.982
DEVIL HUNTER TOKYO HQ BUILDING

05:19.361 --> 05:20.987
What are these horns?

05:20.988 --> 05:24.241
Power, you drank too much blood,
didn't you?

05:24.908 --> 05:26.325
Maybe you drank too much blood

05:26.326 --> 05:28.661
in that fight against the zombies.

05:28.662 --> 05:31.623
- We've got to drain some blood out of you.
- Okay!

05:32.249 --> 05:33.416
Drain her blood?

05:33.417 --> 05:36.003
Power has to have her blood drained
every once in a while,

05:36.795 --> 05:38.921
or else she becomes even more scary

05:38.922 --> 05:41.133
and self-centered than she normally is.

05:41.842 --> 05:43.760
-  So that's why... Denji...
- Huh?

05:43.761 --> 05:46.138
Is it okay if I borrow Power for a while?

05:47.931 --> 05:49.016
Hmm...

05:52.603 --> 05:54.145
Take as long as you need.

05:56.148 --> 05:58.901
As for who's going to be your new buddy
while I'm borrowing her,

05:59.568 --> 06:01.820
this guy said
he wants to team up with you.

06:06.992 --> 06:09.453
Lord Chainsaw! Lord Chainsaw!

06:14.124 --> 06:16.251
Who is this guy?

06:16.960 --> 06:18.045
He's the Shark Fiend.

06:18.629 --> 06:21.506
Normally, he's so ferocious that no one
can even have a conversation with him.

06:21.507 --> 06:23.841
But he said that as long as he gets
to pair up with you, Denji,

06:23.842 --> 06:26.845
- he'll do whatever you tell him to.
- He'll do whatever I tell him to do?

06:27.429 --> 06:29.889
- How come?
- I'm not sure.

06:29.890 --> 06:31.390
Maybe it's because your faces look alike.

06:31.391 --> 06:34.393
Lord Chainsaw! I'll do whatever you say!
No matter what! Lord Chainsaw!

06:34.394 --> 06:37.396
You're the best! You're the greatest!
Lord Chainsaw! You're the greatest!

06:37.397 --> 06:40.025
Don't touch me! I'm not into men.

06:45.447 --> 06:48.492
Hmm? You look unhappy.

06:50.744 --> 06:52.663
I feel great.

06:56.792 --> 06:58.501
If you really are feeling great,

06:58.502 --> 07:01.421
then how about going on a date
with me tomorrow on our day off?

07:02.381 --> 07:03.423
A date?

07:07.427 --> 07:10.931
Hooray! Hooray!

07:12.432 --> 07:14.685
Huh? Denji, you're already here.

07:15.269 --> 07:17.645
You're an hour early.

07:20.566 --> 07:22.984
<i>She's so cute! She's so cute!</i>

07:22.985 --> 07:24.820
She's so cute!

07:25.404 --> 07:27.488
Denji, what time did you get here?

07:27.489 --> 07:30.033
I couldn't sleep last night.
I got here at 5:00.

07:30.617 --> 07:33.036
So... what's the plan for today?

07:33.954 --> 07:37.207
I've never hung out with a girl before.

07:38.041 --> 07:43.463
Today, from now until midnight,
we're going to go movie-theater hopping.

07:44.715 --> 07:45.715
What?

07:54.975 --> 07:58.604
<i>Well, this isn't what I was expecting.</i>

08:02.065 --> 08:03.858
<i>Everyone's laughing.</i>

08:03.859 --> 08:06.360
<i>It wasn't that funny!</i>

08:11.450 --> 08:13.744
<i>Makima's not laughing either.</i>

08:14.494 --> 08:16.121
<i>She's so cute.</i>

08:18.290 --> 08:19.917
That was disappointing.

08:20.417 --> 08:22.251
It wasn't very interesting at all.

08:22.252 --> 08:25.130
It looked like they spent a lot of money
making that movie though.

08:26.632 --> 08:29.009
Well, then... let's go to the next one.

08:39.853 --> 08:41.104
<i>Everyone's crying.</i>

08:43.857 --> 08:45.691
<i>She's not crying.</i>

08:45.692 --> 08:46.777
<i>She's so cute.</i>

08:48.111 --> 08:50.112
That was disappointing.

08:50.113 --> 08:53.908
I didn't like how it felt
when they were trying to force us to cry.

08:57.996 --> 09:00.164
At least the music was good.

09:02.417 --> 09:04.794
The story seemed so fake.

09:09.716 --> 09:11.802
It was just average.

09:12.427 --> 09:14.178
The next movie is the last one.

09:14.179 --> 09:15.263
CINEMA

09:15.264 --> 09:18.642
Everyone says this movie
is hard to understand.

09:19.768 --> 09:21.395
Do you want to try watching it, Denji?

09:23.897 --> 09:27.191
Honestly, all the movies
we've seen today are bad.

09:27.192 --> 09:30.070
Maybe I don't get movies or something.

09:30.862 --> 09:35.491
I only find one good movie
for every ten movies I watch too.

09:35.492 --> 09:36.784
Huh?

09:36.785 --> 09:41.206
But one of those
was a movie that changed my life.

10:27.294 --> 10:29.296
<i>Huh? Whoa.</i>

10:30.422 --> 10:33.008
<i>This scene isn't even that important.</i>

10:33.633 --> 10:36.053
<i>I hope Makima doesn't see me!</i>

10:54.237 --> 10:58.032
I'm never going to forget that last scene
until the day I die.

10:58.033 --> 10:59.283
Me too.

10:59.284 --> 11:02.120
That last movie made
the price of the ticket worth it.

11:06.124 --> 11:09.878
Makima, do you think I have a heart?

11:11.129 --> 11:13.131
Why are you asking that question?

11:14.549 --> 11:15.592
Just because.

11:39.282 --> 11:40.533
You do.

11:40.534 --> 11:42.702
I...

11:43.703 --> 11:45.122
I do.

12:13.316 --> 12:14.650
<i>I see...</i>

12:14.651 --> 12:18.904
<i>The fact that I felt butterflies
means that I do have a heart!</i>

12:18.905 --> 12:21.991
Donations, please!
Donations, please! Donations, please!

12:21.992 --> 12:25.954
We're collecting donations for children
who've been victimized by devils.

12:26.580 --> 12:28.080
Donations, please!

12:28.081 --> 12:31.001
I have a heart,
so I can even make a donation!

12:32.502 --> 12:33.753
Thank you very much!

12:34.379 --> 12:37.507
We're giving away flowers
to everyone who makes a donation.

12:38.133 --> 12:39.718
Ah...

12:40.469 --> 12:41.470
It's beautiful.

12:42.220 --> 12:43.513
Huh?

12:48.351 --> 12:50.352
<i>And the fact that
I can feel that the flower is beautiful</i>

12:50.353 --> 12:52.688
<i>also means I have a heart!</i>

12:52.689 --> 12:53.773
Huh?

12:55.775 --> 12:57.777
<i>Makima, you're incredible.</i>

12:58.904 --> 13:01.615
<i>I feel so much better
after talking to you!</i>

13:03.533 --> 13:07.536
<i>Makima said that once I've gathered
all the pieces of the Gun Devil's flesh,</i>

13:07.537 --> 13:09.079
<i>she'll grant me one wish.</i>

13:09.080 --> 13:13.043
<i>In that case... I think I want
to ask her to be my girlfriend.</i>

13:22.219 --> 13:25.513
<i>Whenever I have a free moment,
I always start thinking about Makima.</i>

13:25.514 --> 13:29.350
<i>I've squeezed other girls' boobs
and kissed other girls before too,</i>

13:29.351 --> 13:32.145
<i>but my heart belongs completely to Makima!</i>

13:32.771 --> 13:35.814
<i>There's no way I'm going
to fall for anyone else!</i>

13:40.403 --> 13:42.072
Run away!

13:43.240 --> 13:44.323
Whoo-hoo!

13:44.324 --> 13:45.616
Water! Water!

13:45.617 --> 13:48.453
Water!

13:49.955 --> 13:50.955
Ah.

13:50.956 --> 13:53.541
Beam! You stay hidden!

13:53.542 --> 13:56.627
If anyone sees you, I won't be able
to walk around in public anymore.

13:56.628 --> 13:57.712
Okay!

13:59.839 --> 14:03.134
Why do fiends all have such weird names?

14:15.522 --> 14:18.108
I should have brought an umbrella.

14:25.615 --> 14:29.618
Whoa!

14:32.122 --> 14:33.665
Hello, hello.

14:34.249 --> 14:36.376
It's raining so hard.

14:37.127 --> 14:39.379
Huh? Uh...

14:39.963 --> 14:41.923
The weather report said...

14:43.633 --> 14:44.676
Hmm?

14:45.468 --> 14:48.013
Huh?

14:49.180 --> 14:50.599
Huh? What's wrong?

14:51.099 --> 14:52.934
Sorry.

14:54.352 --> 14:55.854
What's wrong with you?

15:00.567 --> 15:03.319
Huh? How come you're crying?

15:03.320 --> 15:05.030
Sorry.

15:05.780 --> 15:06.990
Your face...

15:07.574 --> 15:09.867
looks like my dog that passed away.

15:09.868 --> 15:13.287
Huh? You're saying I'm a dog?

15:13.288 --> 15:15.915
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

15:20.253 --> 15:22.297
Hmm? Are you okay?

15:25.300 --> 15:26.760
Uh...

15:28.970 --> 15:31.431
Hold on! I've got a handkerchief!

15:34.017 --> 15:35.769
Ta-da!

15:36.436 --> 15:37.895
What?

15:37.896 --> 15:39.022
A magic trick?

15:39.689 --> 15:40.982
That's amazing!

15:41.816 --> 15:44.319
There's no trick to it.

15:48.114 --> 15:49.324
Thanks.

16:03.588 --> 16:05.423
Ah. It stopped raining!

16:06.841 --> 16:10.177
I work at a café called Crossroads
right down there.

16:10.178 --> 16:12.430
If you drop by,
I'll pay you back for this.

16:13.556 --> 16:15.016
Make sure you come, okay?

16:56.975 --> 16:57.976
All right.

16:58.601 --> 17:01.603
You're late.
I'm going to deduct it from your pay.

17:01.604 --> 17:02.731
You're so stingy!

17:03.356 --> 17:05.107
Take this water to table four.

17:05.108 --> 17:07.861
Stingy! Stingy! Stingy! Stingy! Stingy!

17:11.948 --> 17:14.241
Th... That was fast!

17:14.242 --> 17:17.786
Huh? You got here faster than me!

17:17.787 --> 17:19.873
Well, I guess you're right.

17:21.374 --> 17:23.500
I just came so that you could pay me back.

17:23.501 --> 17:25.462
Hmm?

17:29.132 --> 17:31.759
- Oh.
- Let's have a drink together!

17:31.760 --> 17:35.388
Hey! Can you bring some coffee
for me and him?

17:36.181 --> 17:38.015
But you work here.

17:38.016 --> 17:40.017
What's the big deal?

17:40.018 --> 17:42.770
We only get customers
in the morning anyway.

17:45.064 --> 17:46.316
Well...

17:47.776 --> 17:49.778
A cup of coffee is my gift back to you!

17:50.695 --> 17:51.780
Do you like coffee?

17:52.447 --> 17:53.573
I'll drink it.

17:58.119 --> 18:02.122
What's with that face?
You're just pretending you're fine!

18:02.123 --> 18:04.291
Coffee tastes bad!

18:04.292 --> 18:06.294
It tastes like it's from the gutter!

18:09.464 --> 18:11.216
You're just like a little kid!

18:13.343 --> 18:16.930
<i>She's touching me a lot,
and she's laughing at my jokes.</i>

18:17.430 --> 18:18.723
<i>Could it be that...</i>

18:19.516 --> 18:21.100
<i>she likes me?</i>

18:22.769 --> 18:24.312
My name's Reze.

18:24.813 --> 18:25.855
What's your name?

18:26.856 --> 18:27.941
Denji.

18:28.858 --> 18:29.859
Denji?

18:30.693 --> 18:32.070
Denji...

18:36.241 --> 18:39.536
Denji, I've never met someone
as interesting as you.

18:41.079 --> 18:43.330
Huh...

18:43.331 --> 18:45.708
<i>I'm sure about it now. She does like me.</i>

18:47.168 --> 18:48.628
<i>What am I going to do?</i>

18:49.254 --> 18:51.840
<i>I like people who like me too.</i>

18:53.049 --> 18:55.134
<i>Makima... help.</i>

18:56.219 --> 18:59.222
<i>I'm going to start falling for this girl.</i>

19:15.363 --> 19:17.906
You've had three already. That's enough.

19:17.907 --> 19:19.409
We're going to go on patrol now.

19:21.286 --> 19:23.745
Eating ice cream made me tired.

19:23.746 --> 19:26.291
I heard that eating takes energy too.

19:31.713 --> 19:34.173
I don't want to work anymore today.

19:35.049 --> 19:36.717
They found out where the Gun Devil is.

19:36.718 --> 19:38.176
There's going to be an expedition.

19:38.177 --> 19:43.057
In order to participate, I need to have
more experience defeating big devils.

19:43.766 --> 19:47.185
That's why I want to
go look for more devils.

19:47.186 --> 19:50.606
You're my buddy. Please help me out.

19:50.607 --> 19:51.983
Huh?

19:55.153 --> 19:56.779
Hmm...

20:00.199 --> 20:03.036
How about I think about it a bit
after I've had another ice cream?

20:04.579 --> 20:05.580
Get up.

20:06.080 --> 20:08.665
If I tell the leadership
that you're useless,

20:08.666 --> 20:11.878
they're going to kill you as a devil.
Are you sure you're okay with that?

20:13.421 --> 20:14.923
Hmm.

20:19.636 --> 20:22.555
I'd rather die than work.

20:25.892 --> 20:28.518
<i>He's the second-most
powerful member of Division 4,</i>

20:28.519 --> 20:29.687
<i>after Captain Kishibe.</i>

20:31.064 --> 20:33.733
At least he would be
if he weren't always so lazy.

20:34.567 --> 20:37.778
If you want to join the expedition
to defeat the Gun Devil,

20:37.779 --> 20:40.615
then you should try
to make good use of him.

20:41.950 --> 20:44.494
I don't think
I can get along well with a devil.

20:45.119 --> 20:47.997
But you get along with Power, right?

20:48.498 --> 20:51.542
We had a fistfight just this morning.

20:53.503 --> 20:56.255
You don't have to become friends.

20:57.006 --> 20:59.926
Just use him for your own benefit.

21:00.510 --> 21:02.803
He's someone
who killed every single person

21:02.804 --> 21:05.138
in the village where he was born.

21:05.139 --> 21:06.683
Or to put it more accurately:

21:07.392 --> 21:10.436
He sucked the lifespans out of them
and transformed them into weapons.

21:11.187 --> 21:12.188
Weapons?

21:12.772 --> 21:16.525
He has the power to transform the
life of anyone he touches into a weapon.

21:16.526 --> 21:20.445
That katana you have
is one of his weapons too.

21:20.446 --> 21:24.032
Those weapons can do things like cut
through ghosts that no one can touch...

21:24.033 --> 21:26.452
and have different special powers.

21:28.287 --> 21:31.373
It's okay if you have to pretend.
Just be friendly with him.

21:31.374 --> 21:33.960
I'm sure he'll be useful to you.

21:55.273 --> 21:56.858
I've eliminated the devil!

21:57.358 --> 22:00.903
Please make sure
not to touch its blood or its flesh!

22:07.660 --> 22:09.871
Whoa, that looks delicious.

22:11.998 --> 22:13.623
Hey you, human.

22:13.624 --> 22:15.209
Come over here.

22:16.377 --> 22:19.337
He must be a private Devil Hunter.

22:19.338 --> 22:21.882
He was being eaten up by this devil.

22:21.883 --> 22:25.136
The lower half of his body
is gone already. He's almost dead.

22:30.808 --> 22:33.895
Kill me. Kill me.

22:34.520 --> 22:37.272
Your power gives you
the ability to kill him painlessly.

22:37.273 --> 22:38.775
Grant him his wish to die.

22:39.275 --> 22:40.651
Huh? No way.

22:41.319 --> 22:43.654
I may be an angel, but I'm also a devil.

22:44.363 --> 22:47.116
I believe that humans
should suffer when they die.

23:06.260 --> 23:08.805
I don't think we can become friends.
Even if I pretend.

23:10.056 --> 23:11.057
I guess not.

23:14.685 --> 23:17.939
<i>Makima's the one
who found my heart.</i>

23:18.523 --> 23:22.318
<i>So that's why my heart belongs to Makima.</i>

23:23.820 --> 23:26.321
<i>But... my body...</i>

23:26.322 --> 23:27.907
<i>It's moving on its own!</i>

23:30.076 --> 23:32.202
Oh, it's you!

23:32.203 --> 23:33.830
I came to have lunch.

23:34.914 --> 23:38.918
The food here's not that good. No one
would come every day for a whole week.

23:39.544 --> 23:40.836
It's good.

23:40.837 --> 23:42.462
It is good.

23:42.463 --> 23:44.423
You have such bad taste.

23:45.550 --> 23:46.926
Well...

23:47.468 --> 23:50.011
I'll have some curry and some ice cream.

23:50.012 --> 23:51.721
Ah! And some fried rice!

23:51.722 --> 23:55.642
How about you come eat
over here at this table?

23:55.643 --> 23:56.726
I'm fine here.

23:56.727 --> 23:59.980
You're studying right now, right?
Even though you're on the clock.

23:59.981 --> 24:02.774
You don't go to school, right?

24:02.775 --> 24:04.735
Even though you're 16.

24:07.488 --> 24:11.199
I think that's even worse.

24:11.200 --> 24:13.160
Do you really think so?

24:13.161 --> 24:14.494
I see.

24:14.495 --> 24:17.497
You're working as a Devil Hunter
instead of going to school.

24:17.498 --> 24:19.876
You're a weird one.

24:25.423 --> 24:28.049
I'm going to study over here.

24:28.050 --> 24:29.886
Scoot over! Scoot over!

24:34.015 --> 24:36.433
I want to learn how to read kanji.

24:36.434 --> 24:38.144
You can't read kanji?

24:38.728 --> 24:40.354
Then I'll teach you!

24:41.439 --> 24:42.648
Here's a question.

24:43.232 --> 24:44.274
Ta-da!

24:44.275 --> 24:46.234
What does this say?

24:46.235 --> 24:48.778
That says "balls," you sex-crazed girl.

24:48.779 --> 24:51.157
So you do know what it says.

24:51.741 --> 24:54.410
"Balls" is the only one I can read.

24:58.372 --> 24:59.832
That's crazy.

25:05.379 --> 25:08.506
I wish I could have
gone to school with you.

25:08.507 --> 25:10.134
It would have been fun.

25:15.890 --> 25:17.725
<i>What am I saying?</i>

25:22.021 --> 25:23.730
Do you want to go with me?

25:23.731 --> 25:25.691
- At night.
- At night?

25:26.317 --> 25:29.820
Let's go explore
a school building together at night.

25:33.908 --> 25:34.909
Okay.

25:35.952 --> 25:38.079
<i>My heart belongs to Makima,</i>

25:39.121 --> 25:42.041
<i>but my body won't listen to me!</i>

25:53.052 --> 25:54.345
Typhoon.

25:55.054 --> 25:56.055
What is it?

25:56.681 --> 26:01.269
Why do you devils want Chainsaw's heart?

26:02.937 --> 26:04.521
You don't need to know.

26:04.522 --> 26:06.982
The only thing you need to focus on
is holding up your end of the contract

26:06.983 --> 26:08.275
between you and me.

26:08.276 --> 26:12.070
Sounds like we're
going to be working together for a while.

26:12.071 --> 26:14.365
So let's get more comfortable
with each other.

26:15.783 --> 26:18.327
Typhoon Devil.

26:21.539 --> 26:26.501
The contract is that once
I get my hands on Chainsaw's heart,

26:26.502 --> 26:28.713
you'll let me use your powers forever.

26:29.213 --> 26:30.380
Be careful.

26:30.381 --> 26:35.344
The human who has Chainsaw's heart
has killed lots of devils.

26:35.928 --> 26:39.348
That's because
the devils aren't very bright.

26:42.685 --> 26:47.355
I killed a Devil Hunter from China
for a job once.

26:47.356 --> 26:52.611
He was a merciless Devil Hunter.
They said he had no blood or tears.

26:53.487 --> 26:55.740
How did you kill him?

27:02.747 --> 27:05.750
I looked for how I could
make him bleed and cry.

27:06.250 --> 27:09.085
I took his wife and kid as hostages.

27:09.086 --> 27:12.130
Then I skinned them
and showed him their hides.

27:12.131 --> 27:14.215
He let me kill him after that.

27:29.023 --> 27:30.441
Denji, aren't you scared?

27:31.484 --> 27:35.195
Uh, I'm not really scared.

27:35.196 --> 27:36.781
This just feels weird.

27:37.365 --> 27:39.909
What do you mean?

27:45.915 --> 27:48.209
Hey. I'm a little scared.

27:49.460 --> 27:50.753
Can I hold your hand?

28:00.554 --> 28:02.097
<i>Makima.</i>

28:02.098 --> 28:04.892
<i>To be honest,
I don't want to hold her hand.</i>

28:06.685 --> 28:09.813
<i>But my body just...</i>

28:14.151 --> 28:16.694
Who knows the answer?

28:16.695 --> 28:18.279
Me! Me! Me!

28:18.280 --> 28:19.656
Two! It's two!

28:19.657 --> 28:21.283
That's right! You're a genius!

28:22.576 --> 28:26.329
- What does this English word mean?
- I have no idea!

28:26.330 --> 28:28.873
The answer is: "Big ass."

28:28.874 --> 28:30.334
You sex-crazed girl!

28:31.460 --> 28:34.546
Huh... So this is what school is like.

28:34.547 --> 28:36.215
I think I've got the hang of it now.

28:37.842 --> 28:41.219
Denji, is it really true that
you didn't even go to elementary school?

28:41.220 --> 28:42.763
Huh? Yeah.

28:43.389 --> 28:47.851
Isn't that... bad?

28:47.852 --> 28:49.353
Bad?

28:50.229 --> 28:51.647
Well, not bad.

28:52.314 --> 28:53.482
It's weird.

28:55.568 --> 28:58.362
A 16-year-old is still a kid.

28:58.863 --> 29:01.114
Normally, you'd study for entrance exams,

29:01.115 --> 29:04.743
join school clubs,
and go out with friends.

29:05.369 --> 29:09.665
But you... you kill devils
and almost get yourself killed by them.

29:10.207 --> 29:12.542
Is Public Safety,
that place you work at now,

29:12.543 --> 29:14.170
is it really a good place?

29:15.880 --> 29:18.632
Well, it's a really good place, you know.

29:19.341 --> 29:21.134
I get to eat three meals a day.

29:21.135 --> 29:22.845
And I get to sleep on a futon.

29:24.680 --> 29:28.017
But that's the bare minimum
for everyone in Japan.

29:28.517 --> 29:30.478
It's something that's normal for everyone.

29:31.562 --> 29:32.980
Uh...

29:34.440 --> 29:37.234
My head's getting hot
from thinking too hard.

29:39.862 --> 29:40.863
In that case...

29:42.406 --> 29:44.283
Do you want to cool down a bit?

29:54.793 --> 29:57.713
It's so cold!

30:05.638 --> 30:08.140
I don't know
how to swim that well, you know.

30:14.647 --> 30:16.440
Hmm?

30:17.691 --> 30:20.152
Then I'll teach you how to swim.

30:24.406 --> 30:27.701
Huh?

30:29.411 --> 30:30.704
Huh?

30:31.288 --> 30:34.707
Take off your clothes.
Your clothes are going to pull you down.

30:34.708 --> 30:36.709
You're so sexy.

30:36.710 --> 30:39.338
Don't you want to learn how to swim?

30:41.131 --> 30:42.883
I am starting to want to learn.

30:48.305 --> 30:50.474
Denji, you should get naked too.

30:51.809 --> 30:54.311
It's dark. I can't see anyway.

30:55.563 --> 30:57.480
- <i>Calm down!</i>
- <i>I can see everything!</i>

30:57.481 --> 30:58.773
<i>It's my first time seeing nipples!</i>

30:58.774 --> 31:01.526
<i>If I take off my clothes now,
I'll be betraying Makima!</i>

31:06.949 --> 31:08.075
<i>Damn!</i>

31:14.081 --> 31:17.334
Come on! Come over here, Denji!

31:18.335 --> 31:22.505
<i>No, Denji.
If I go, then my heart will go too.</i>

31:22.506 --> 31:24.757
I know what's going on.

31:24.758 --> 31:27.885
You're scared to get in the pool
because you can't swim.

31:31.473 --> 31:33.683
Come on! It feels good!

31:34.935 --> 31:36.436
Hurry up! Come on!

32:56.308 --> 32:57.476
I'll teach you.

32:58.936 --> 33:01.312
I'll teach you things you don't know.

33:01.313 --> 33:02.856
Things you don't know how to do.

33:03.941 --> 33:07.069
I'll teach you everything.

33:13.367 --> 33:15.618
Denji! Breathe! Breathe!

33:29.842 --> 33:31.217
It's raining!

33:31.218 --> 33:32.344
Yeah!

33:36.849 --> 33:37.974
Hyah!

33:55.743 --> 33:58.412
-  The rain's not stopping.
-  Mmm.

34:05.669 --> 34:07.212
Denji...

34:07.880 --> 34:10.924
The country mouse or the city mouse.

34:11.508 --> 34:13.051
Which one would you rather be?

34:14.011 --> 34:15.304
What are you talking about?

34:16.513 --> 34:18.474
It's one of Aesop's fables.

34:21.393 --> 34:24.270
The country mouse lives a safe life,

34:24.271 --> 34:26.690
but doesn't have delicious food
like the city mouse.

34:27.608 --> 34:30.818
The city mouse can find good food,

34:30.819 --> 34:33.572
but he's in danger of getting killed
by a cat or a human.

34:38.035 --> 34:40.496
I wanted to be the country mouse.

34:41.663 --> 34:46.502
But Makima captured me
and brought me to the city.

34:51.173 --> 34:53.425
My heart belongs in the countryside.

34:54.009 --> 34:57.346
I don't want to follow around a city mouse
like you and put myself in danger.

34:59.223 --> 35:00.224
Hey...

35:04.520 --> 35:07.104
I want to be the city mouse.

35:07.105 --> 35:08.272
What?

35:08.273 --> 35:10.942
Being the country mouse is better!

35:10.943 --> 35:13.152
A peaceful life is what's best.

35:13.153 --> 35:15.279
The city has more good food.

35:15.280 --> 35:16.572
And it looks fun.

35:16.573 --> 35:20.785
Are you saying
you just want to eat and have fun?

35:20.786 --> 35:22.162
Yeah.

35:25.582 --> 35:29.126
In that case, there's a festival
going on nearby tomorrow.

35:29.127 --> 35:32.673
Do you want to go together?
I'm sure it'll be fun. And delicious.

35:34.967 --> 35:37.301
I can go if it's after work.

35:37.302 --> 35:40.848
Yay! It's a promise, okay?

35:43.392 --> 35:46.018
I'm going to the restroom.

35:52.359 --> 35:54.027
She's so damn cute.

37:02.596 --> 37:03.805
Denji?

37:08.602 --> 37:12.105
That's right. I'm Denji.

37:13.357 --> 37:17.653
I was just about to go pee myself.

37:22.074 --> 37:24.368
Let's go to the bathroom together.

37:25.202 --> 37:26.536
Okay?

37:36.588 --> 37:37.589
Pochita.

37:38.173 --> 37:40.342
I have feelings
for two different people now.

37:41.969 --> 37:43.428
Do you know who I'm talking about?

37:44.805 --> 37:46.515
<i>I'm not talking about that angel.</i>

37:47.140 --> 37:48.808
<i>He's a guy.</i>

37:55.273 --> 37:58.192
<i>The small girl has a pretty face,</i>

37:58.193 --> 38:00.528
<i>but she tried to kill me.</i>

38:02.823 --> 38:04.574
Come on!

38:05.242 --> 38:08.577
<i>Power still tries to
kill me sometimes too.</i>

38:08.578 --> 38:10.287
<i>She's a narcissist, she's selfish,</i>

38:10.288 --> 38:13.125
<i>she's a pathological liar,
and she's a bigot.</i>

38:14.835 --> 38:16.836
How come you're running away?

38:16.837 --> 38:19.715
You promised you'd go
to the bathroom with me!

38:24.803 --> 38:26.304
<i>What am I going to do?</i>

38:27.931 --> 38:30.809
<i>When I close my eyes, there's two of them!</i>

38:33.186 --> 38:34.980
<i>Pochita. Which one would you choose?</i>

38:58.754 --> 39:00.172
Hello!

39:01.298 --> 39:03.925
Are you going to pee on the roof?

39:04.426 --> 39:06.845
Who... Who are you?

39:09.973 --> 39:11.682
You're asking me,

39:11.683 --> 39:14.436
but do you have any idea who you are?

39:15.353 --> 39:17.646
I know who you are.

39:17.647 --> 39:19.733
You're a piece of cheese.

39:20.317 --> 39:23.445
You're a piece of cheese
for luring out the mouse.

39:23.945 --> 39:26.656
What are you talking about? Please stop!

39:28.116 --> 39:31.619
I'm going to skin your face,
carve out your eyes

39:31.620 --> 39:33.412
and show it all to Chainsaw!

39:33.413 --> 39:35.373
And this is what I'm going to tell him.

39:36.374 --> 39:40.587
"Your precious woman is still alive."

39:43.882 --> 39:45.466
And whenever I do that,

39:45.467 --> 39:48.886
everyone starts listening to me
for some reason.

39:48.887 --> 39:50.930
Then all that's left
for me to do is to kill him.

39:50.931 --> 39:55.060
The only piece of your body I want
is your skin and your eyeballs!

39:56.186 --> 39:59.231
I don't need to take your life!

40:38.478 --> 40:42.022
<i>♪ I have a date with Jane today ♪</i>

40:42.023 --> 40:43.983
<i>♪ All is ready ♪</i>

40:43.984 --> 40:49.114
<i>♪ In the morning
We'll go to church together ♪</i>

40:49.823 --> 40:53.618
<i>♪ We will drink coffee ♪</i>

40:55.162 --> 40:59.166
<i>♪ And eat omelets at a café ♪</i>

41:00.625 --> 41:04.295
<i>♪ After a walk ♪</i>

41:04.296 --> 41:09.050
<i>♪ In a park ♪</i>

41:10.051 --> 41:13.847
<i>♪ We will go to an aquarium ♪</i>

41:15.557 --> 41:19.352
<i>♪ And we will see dolphins and penguins ♪</i>

41:20.896 --> 41:25.734
<i>♪ Loved by Jane ♪</i>

41:26.234 --> 41:29.653
<i>♪ We will rest after lunch ♪</i>

41:29.654 --> 41:35.076
<i>♪ So, what did we do in the morning? ♪</i>

41:35.785 --> 41:39.748
<i>♪ We will speak about it ♪</i>

41:41.166 --> 41:45.003
<i>♪ Until we remember ♪</i>

41:46.463 --> 41:50.467
<i>♪ We won't remember ♪</i>

41:51.509 --> 41:56.556
<i>♪ And we will sleep
At the church that night ♪</i>

42:25.877 --> 42:28.588
You're the one who made the storm
to trap us inside the building.

42:29.172 --> 42:30.173
Right, Typhoon?

42:31.049 --> 42:33.718
I didn't know you were here, Lady Reze.

42:34.469 --> 42:36.804
I'll turn a blind eye
to what you did today.

42:36.805 --> 42:39.390
In exchange, you'll obey me for a while.

42:39.391 --> 42:42.227
Go deal with his body.

42:59.911 --> 43:02.371
Hmm.

43:02.372 --> 43:03.790
Huh?

43:15.760 --> 43:17.429
- Boo!
- Whoa!

44:49.104 --> 44:53.023
I heard about this place
from the owner of the café I work at.

44:53.024 --> 44:55.192
He said it's the best spot
to watch fireworks.

44:55.193 --> 44:58.029
No one else ever comes here.
It's a secret spot.

44:58.988 --> 45:01.032
Huh...

45:15.046 --> 45:16.297
Hey, Denji.

45:17.006 --> 45:19.050
I've been thinking a lot these days.

45:20.051 --> 45:23.303
I think your current situation is weird.

45:23.304 --> 45:26.306
You're only 16,
but they're not letting you go to school.

45:26.307 --> 45:28.309
And they're making you kill devils.

45:28.893 --> 45:30.937
It's not something
this country should allow.

45:37.527 --> 45:40.447
Why don't you quit your job
and run away with me.

45:40.989 --> 45:43.908
I'll make you happy.

45:44.742 --> 45:46.536
I'll protect you
for the rest of your life.

45:47.912 --> 45:49.080
Please.

45:54.627 --> 45:57.338
Run away? Where?

45:58.173 --> 45:59.965
I'll ask my friend.

45:59.966 --> 46:03.427
My friend has a place
where Public Safety will never find you.

46:03.428 --> 46:05.429
It won't happen right away,

46:05.430 --> 46:07.515
but we can go to school
together there someday.

46:08.725 --> 46:10.518
Why would you do all that for me?

46:11.936 --> 46:13.605
Because...

46:14.397 --> 46:16.274
I like you, Denji.

46:26.284 --> 46:28.578
Why are you having
such a hard time deciding?

46:29.537 --> 46:31.206
Denji, do you hate me?

46:31.789 --> 46:33.082
I like you!

46:34.459 --> 46:35.460
But...

46:36.044 --> 46:39.047
I've just recently started
to feel appreciated at work.

46:39.714 --> 46:42.467
I can go farther away without supervision.

46:43.468 --> 46:47.347
I'm gradually learning how to deal with
my buddy, who has a shitty personality.

46:48.806 --> 46:52.560
And I've finally started to become friends
with my difficult senior colleague.

46:53.686 --> 46:56.147
And I've found a goal
to work towards at work.

46:56.940 --> 46:59.359
Things are starting to get fun now.

47:00.693 --> 47:04.739
Can't I keep seeing you
while I continue to work?

47:07.951 --> 47:10.495
- The fireworks are about to begin!
- This way, please!

47:13.373 --> 47:14.499
I see.

47:15.166 --> 47:16.209
I understand.

47:18.753 --> 47:19.754
Denji.

47:20.588 --> 47:24.299
There's someone else you like, right?

48:47.258 --> 48:48.426
It hurts, doesn't it?

48:48.926 --> 48:50.428
I'm sorry.

48:58.394 --> 49:01.814
Denji, I'm going to take your heart. Okay?

49:08.279 --> 49:10.322
Dash!

49:10.323 --> 49:11.824
Huh?

49:19.290 --> 49:21.958
Run away! Run away!
We're in trouble! We're in trouble!

49:21.959 --> 49:25.087
How come I didn't notice anything
from the smell?

49:25.088 --> 49:27.589
She's dangerous, Lord Chainsaw!

49:27.590 --> 49:30.510
That smell...

49:31.177 --> 49:34.889
She's the Bomb Devil!

49:38.935 --> 49:40.311
Boom.

50:06.170 --> 50:07.171
You thief.

50:35.199 --> 50:36.492
Lord Chainsaw!

50:50.631 --> 50:53.300
Are you from Division 4 too?

50:53.301 --> 50:56.220
I'll let you go if you leave Denji there
and leave right now.

51:03.978 --> 51:05.772
Oh. I see.

51:20.244 --> 51:21.746
Hmm?

51:35.510 --> 51:38.971
Damn. I wanted to go to the festival.

51:39.472 --> 51:41.640
Whoa. She's killing something.

51:41.641 --> 51:44.185
We've encountered a devil
near the festival.

51:45.144 --> 51:47.188
2034.

51:47.855 --> 51:49.607
The battle begins.

51:50.274 --> 51:52.692
Are you private Devil Hunters?

51:52.693 --> 51:54.778
Whoa. She said something.

51:54.779 --> 51:56.864
This one's really strong.

52:17.885 --> 52:19.387
They sure ran away fast!

52:20.555 --> 52:22.473
DEVIL EXTERMINATION DIVISION 2
FUCHŪ TRAINING FACILITY

52:34.443 --> 52:35.653
Match over!

52:36.279 --> 52:37.989
Thank you.

52:40.283 --> 52:42.994
Thank you for your instruction.

52:44.370 --> 52:45.705
Aki.

52:46.581 --> 52:49.332
Thanks for coming.

52:49.333 --> 52:51.418
I can't say no to you, Nomo.

52:51.419 --> 52:55.714
Whoa! Really?
Then come back to Division 2!

52:55.715 --> 52:59.342
All the stories I hear about
the Special Division sound so gory anyway.

52:59.343 --> 53:03.513
If everything goes well, I'm going
to become the sub-captain in five years.

53:03.514 --> 53:06.100
When that happens,
I'm going to invite you to join.

53:07.894 --> 53:09.353
Thank you very much.

53:12.565 --> 53:13.608
<i>Hey.</i>

53:14.233 --> 53:16.694
You haven't told him
that you'll be dead in five years?

53:17.862 --> 53:20.363
Who did you hear that from?

53:20.364 --> 53:21.866
From Power.

53:22.491 --> 53:23.951
That damn devil.

53:25.453 --> 53:26.996
Don't tell anyone.

53:28.706 --> 53:30.498
You're so lucky.

53:30.499 --> 53:32.668
I want to die soon too.

53:33.836 --> 53:36.546
As long as I'm alive, I have to work hard.

53:36.547 --> 53:38.716
If I die,
I won't have to work hard anymore.

53:40.217 --> 53:41.719
Oh, that reminds me...

53:42.303 --> 53:44.680
You have a contract
with the Future Devil, right?

53:45.181 --> 53:46.890
Why don't you try asking it?

53:46.891 --> 53:48.684
Ask it when I'm going to die.

53:49.936 --> 53:51.145
I refuse.

53:52.730 --> 53:55.523
Aki! Come downstairs! Now!

53:57.276 --> 54:00.237
He showed up at the entrance and
claimed he's from the Special Division.

54:01.238 --> 54:03.907
Is this fiend really on our side?

54:03.908 --> 54:05.409
Y-Yes.

54:05.910 --> 54:09.163
Did a devil do this to Denji?

54:10.247 --> 54:13.042
Bomb is coming... Bomb...

54:13.709 --> 54:16.294
She's one of the Gun Devil's allies!

54:18.297 --> 54:20.674
How do you know that?

54:23.010 --> 54:24.178
Answer me.

54:24.804 --> 54:27.431
I could kill you right here
if I wanted to.

54:28.516 --> 54:30.558
If I tell you, they'll kill me.

54:30.559 --> 54:32.435
I promised Makima.

54:32.436 --> 54:33.937
Makima?

54:33.938 --> 54:35.563
Ah!

54:35.564 --> 54:37.692
There she is! Bomb's here!

54:45.491 --> 54:46.867
Hey, beautiful lady!

54:47.493 --> 54:49.495
Don't come any closer!

54:49.996 --> 54:52.706
This place is a training facility
for Devil Extermination Division 2.

54:52.707 --> 54:55.543
Members of the public
are not allowed to enter.

54:57.336 --> 54:59.170
Excuse me!

55:01.257 --> 55:02.298
Reze...

55:02.299 --> 55:03.675
Reze?

55:03.676 --> 55:06.219
Please help me!

55:06.220 --> 55:08.931
I'm being attacked by a devil!

55:09.557 --> 55:10.557
Oh.

55:10.558 --> 55:13.268
She's sure smiling a lot
for someone under attack.

55:13.269 --> 55:15.228
- Nomo.
- Yeah.

55:15.229 --> 55:17.439
Take your friend with you
and stay in the back.

55:17.440 --> 55:18.690
Okay.

55:18.691 --> 55:22.610
Contact headquarters and the vice-captain.
Summon all Division 2 members.

55:22.611 --> 55:24.154
Okay!

55:24.155 --> 55:25.322
And...

55:25.990 --> 55:28.701
Have you seen that beauty
somewhere before?

55:29.285 --> 55:31.703
Now's not the right time
to try to pick up women.

55:31.704 --> 55:34.206
No, I'm being serious.

55:37.501 --> 55:40.587
It can't be true. There's no way.

55:40.588 --> 55:43.339
Thanks. I'm counting on you.

55:43.340 --> 55:44.717
You owe me one.

55:46.635 --> 55:48.220
Kato! Tanabe!

55:49.096 --> 55:51.681
I'll treat you to dinner
if you can kill that woman.

55:51.682 --> 55:54.727
Don't assume she's a human.
Handle her like you would a devil.

55:55.352 --> 55:58.063
I guess it didn't work.

55:58.064 --> 55:59.607
It's not working.

56:00.900 --> 56:02.610
In that case, I've got no choice.

56:04.737 --> 56:06.989
I'll just have to kill everyone.

56:13.329 --> 56:14.496
Blood?

56:14.497 --> 56:17.166
We've caused mold to grow
in her heart and intestines.

56:17.666 --> 56:20.251
She's throwing up blood. It's working.

56:20.252 --> 56:23.255
Even if she drinks blood and regenerates,
the mold's not going to disappear.

56:24.173 --> 56:26.258
Now we just need to buy some time.

56:29.345 --> 56:30.513
Hmm?

56:33.516 --> 56:35.059
She inflicted damage to herself!

56:37.895 --> 56:39.604
Are you able to grow mold on her brain?

56:39.605 --> 56:41.816
We can only do it if the target's alive.

56:51.408 --> 56:52.534
Boo.

57:00.417 --> 57:02.836
She's a devil! A devil is here!

57:02.837 --> 57:05.672
She went right!
Don't let her get near Aki!

57:05.673 --> 57:07.383
Nomo! Behind you!

57:09.885 --> 57:11.137
Kon!

57:15.599 --> 57:17.059
Ah--

57:28.737 --> 57:31.490
There she is! There's the devil!

57:34.952 --> 57:37.495
Masaki Ando,
requesting permission to fire!

57:37.496 --> 57:38.873
Permission granted!

57:50.342 --> 57:52.595
In Japan,
do you need permission to fire a gun?

57:53.929 --> 57:54.930
Kon!

58:00.936 --> 58:02.938
You're pretty stubborn.

58:04.023 --> 58:06.859
Now that's a real sight for sore eyes.

58:12.448 --> 58:13.657
Kon.

58:20.581 --> 58:22.498
Excuse me for a moment.

58:22.499 --> 58:24.250
Vice-captain!

58:24.251 --> 58:27.338
That was close.

58:28.547 --> 58:31.132
What's that taste?

58:31.133 --> 58:34.469
- Huh?
-  I hate this taste.

58:34.470 --> 58:35.679
I'm going home now.

58:40.267 --> 58:42.811
I was supposed to go
to a singles mixer today.

58:43.312 --> 58:46.065
Take me with you next time.

58:47.983 --> 58:51.361
I'll drive. You have them
drink some of your blood.

58:51.362 --> 58:52.946
Huh?

58:52.947 --> 58:54.615
I guess I've got no choice.

58:58.202 --> 59:00.621
Aren't you going to start the car?

59:01.455 --> 59:02.873
Damn.

59:03.457 --> 59:06.376
It showed me a future
I didn't want to see.

59:06.377 --> 59:07.460
Huh?

59:18.722 --> 59:20.390
That monster.

59:20.391 --> 59:24.143
I killed them to show you
how powerful I am.

59:24.144 --> 59:26.522
I don't want to kill anyone if possible.

59:27.856 --> 59:30.858
Take Denji out of the car and leave.

59:45.958 --> 59:49.670
The gasoline is going to
make that car burn to a crisp.

59:53.841 --> 59:56.218
What a pain.

59:57.761 --> 59:59.263
Acho!

01:00:03.851 --> 01:00:05.852
I asked the Special Division for backup.

01:00:05.853 --> 01:00:07.146
They saved us.

01:00:13.736 --> 01:00:15.112
No way!

01:00:16.655 --> 01:00:19.616
I kicked with everything I got just now.

01:00:20.576 --> 01:00:22.161
Nice kick.

01:00:25.748 --> 01:00:26.999
Want to fight?

01:00:28.542 --> 01:00:31.627
Kobeni! We're changing strategies!

01:00:32.880 --> 01:00:36.090
This one's a lot stronger than us!

01:00:36.091 --> 01:00:38.385
Time for a strategic retreat!

01:00:38.969 --> 01:00:40.429
Anyways, bye.

01:00:45.684 --> 01:00:48.269
My legs... My legs...

01:00:48.270 --> 01:00:50.105
My legs gave out...

01:00:51.315 --> 01:00:54.109
My legs... My legs...

01:00:59.114 --> 01:01:02.116
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

01:01:02.117 --> 01:01:04.953
I'll quit my job. So please forgive me!

01:01:25.516 --> 01:01:26.517
There she is!

01:01:34.149 --> 01:01:37.902
Hey. Chainsaw's awake now.

01:01:37.903 --> 01:01:40.447
But the bomb girl's right behind us.

01:01:41.990 --> 01:01:44.033
Shit! Damn!

01:01:44.034 --> 01:01:47.036
The transmitter's broken on this car.

01:01:48.372 --> 01:01:50.124
What's wrong with this car?

01:01:51.250 --> 01:01:54.043
If it comes down to it,
I'm going to crash this car into her!

01:01:54.044 --> 01:01:56.797
I can't let her have Denji!

01:01:58.632 --> 01:02:00.383
What's going on?

01:02:00.384 --> 01:02:02.427
He's cutting the top of the car!

01:02:02.428 --> 01:02:03.637
Huh?

01:02:06.598 --> 01:02:07.890
Stop, Denji!

01:02:07.891 --> 01:02:09.893
You haven't had that much blood yet!

01:02:11.103 --> 01:02:14.230
It hurt so much,
I thought I was going to die.

01:02:14.231 --> 01:02:17.316
My brain's all mixed-up.

01:02:17.317 --> 01:02:19.945
But I spent some time
looking back on what's happened.

01:02:21.280 --> 01:02:24.198
And I just realized

01:02:24.199 --> 01:02:27.786
that every single girl I ever meet
always tries to kill me!

01:02:28.370 --> 01:02:32.123
Everyone always wants Chainsaw's heart!

01:02:32.124 --> 01:02:36.294
Doesn't anyone want Denji's heart? Huh?

01:02:36.295 --> 01:02:40.047
I really do like you, Denji. It's true.

01:02:40.048 --> 01:02:42.049
Huh? Really?

01:02:44.636 --> 01:02:47.973
Don't listen to the enemy!
You're so gullible!

01:02:50.267 --> 01:02:53.812
That was close.
I was about to get tricked.

01:02:54.396 --> 01:02:57.607
I don't know why you're trying to kill me.

01:02:57.608 --> 01:02:59.818
But I don't care!

01:03:00.527 --> 01:03:02.571
I've got Makima!

01:03:03.405 --> 01:03:04.822
Makima?

01:03:04.823 --> 01:03:09.452
Denji, I didn't know that witch
has got you in the palm of her hand.

01:03:09.453 --> 01:03:12.580
Then it would have been no use
even if we ran away together.

01:03:12.581 --> 01:03:14.248
Aw.

01:03:14.249 --> 01:03:17.586
I wish I never kissed you! Aw.

01:03:20.797 --> 01:03:22.131
If anyone else dies because of me,

01:03:22.132 --> 01:03:25.052
I'm going to have trouble getting
out of bed in the morning.

01:03:26.178 --> 01:03:28.846
I'm going to arrest you!

01:03:28.847 --> 01:03:30.848
Come here, Denji.

01:03:30.849 --> 01:03:34.602
I'm going to show you how we fight.

01:03:34.603 --> 01:03:37.314
Then show me!

01:04:00.170 --> 01:04:03.297
Denji. You're not applying
what you've learned.

01:04:03.298 --> 01:04:06.133
You can't just swing
your chainsaws around.

01:04:06.134 --> 01:04:08.928
You've got to understand
your own power better.

01:04:08.929 --> 01:04:10.055
Huh?

01:04:13.684 --> 01:04:14.726
Boom.

01:05:08.697 --> 01:05:09.990
Regeneration?

01:05:11.033 --> 01:05:12.617
So you were revving the engine

01:05:12.618 --> 01:05:14.911
before you got kicked.

01:05:49.237 --> 01:05:50.572
You Devil!

01:06:10.717 --> 01:06:12.969
<i>If I mess up even
a single move, I'm going to die.</i>

01:06:13.637 --> 01:06:17.099
<i>I can see the future,
but only a few seconds in advance.</i>

01:06:17.683 --> 01:06:20.060
<i>I don't know if my body
will be able to react in time.</i>

01:06:26.024 --> 01:06:27.651
<i>Perfect judgment.</i>

01:06:32.948 --> 01:06:34.157
<i>Perfect judgment.</i>

01:06:36.201 --> 01:06:37.994
<i>Perfect judgment.</i>

01:06:43.792 --> 01:06:45.210
<i>Perfect--</i>

01:06:52.676 --> 01:06:53.884
That was close!

01:06:53.885 --> 01:06:56.888
Sorry I'm late.

01:06:57.472 --> 01:07:00.057
This is the first time I've ever
wanted to be friends with a Devil!

01:07:00.058 --> 01:07:01.393
Here you go.

01:07:04.896 --> 01:07:07.064
Time-out!

01:07:07.065 --> 01:07:09.900
I'm anemic
and I'm almost naked over here.

01:07:09.901 --> 01:07:12.153
And you've got the two of you.
That's not fair.

01:07:12.154 --> 01:07:15.656
You're right. Should we give her a break?

01:07:15.657 --> 01:07:17.032
No.

01:07:17.033 --> 01:07:19.160
That's what he said. Sorry!

01:07:19.161 --> 01:07:20.370
The time-out is over.

01:07:26.585 --> 01:07:30.797
Lady Reze! Typhoon is here!

01:07:31.965 --> 01:07:33.884
That's not fair!

01:07:52.903 --> 01:07:53.987
It's okay.

01:07:54.821 --> 01:07:56.740
You're going to go to heaven.

01:08:01.995 --> 01:08:03.788
I'm going to take your blood.

01:08:03.789 --> 01:08:05.040
Sorry.

01:08:26.228 --> 01:08:29.063
A normal devil would have been dead.

01:08:29.064 --> 01:08:32.192
You're so impressive, Lord Chainsaw!
You're amazing!

01:08:33.109 --> 01:08:36.070
Your girlfriend has killed
too many people.

01:08:36.071 --> 01:08:39.449
If we let her run free,
then many more will die.

01:08:40.408 --> 01:08:43.077
Chainsaw. Make your choice.

01:08:43.078 --> 01:08:47.081
<i>Either let her kill you
and minimize the damage,</i>

01:08:47.082 --> 01:08:48.917
<i>or kill her instead.</i>

01:08:51.044 --> 01:08:54.297
Well, that's an easy decision.

01:08:55.423 --> 01:08:57.884
Reze is incredibly powerful, though.

01:08:59.970 --> 01:09:03.390
Shark, you know
about the Chainsaw Devil, right?

01:09:03.974 --> 01:09:07.477
If you don't want to die today,
then you should tell us what you know.

01:09:09.479 --> 01:09:12.648
Lord Chainsaw runs really fast!

01:09:12.649 --> 01:09:17.486
But when he goes places,
he doesn't just use his legs.

01:09:17.487 --> 01:09:20.197
He uses the chains on his chainsaws
to get around.

01:09:20.198 --> 01:09:22.074
He flings his chains through the air
and hooks them on buildings,

01:09:22.075 --> 01:09:24.118
and then he swings
from building to building!

01:09:24.119 --> 01:09:28.414
I see! Samurai Sword
draws his sword to get around.

01:09:28.415 --> 01:09:31.166
And Reze uses explosions.

01:09:31.167 --> 01:09:33.544
I need to apply my own powers too!

01:09:33.545 --> 01:09:36.839
Lord Chainsaw, you're a genius!
Lord Chainsaw, you're a genius!

01:09:36.840 --> 01:09:41.595
I should use chains to get around!
I see! I get it!

01:09:43.305 --> 01:09:46.098
That's right! That's right!

01:09:46.099 --> 01:09:47.975
I'm going to try it!

01:09:47.976 --> 01:09:50.896
- Beam! Turn into a shark!
- Okay!

01:09:53.356 --> 01:09:54.357
Huh?

01:09:55.442 --> 01:09:57.903
This is it!

01:09:59.195 --> 01:10:04.534
I'm going to use chains to control Beam,
and Beam is going to run like a horse!

01:10:06.161 --> 01:10:08.787
That's not it...
That's not it...

01:10:08.788 --> 01:10:11.373
Are you sure? I don't think that's it.

01:10:11.374 --> 01:10:14.335
I think you're supposed to shoot out
the chains from your arms

01:10:14.336 --> 01:10:16.003
and hook them onto buildings.

01:10:16.004 --> 01:10:19.757
Huh? This is the right way! Right, Beam?

01:10:19.758 --> 01:10:22.009
You're right! You're right! You're right!

01:10:22.010 --> 01:10:24.428
All right! Run, Beam!

01:10:24.429 --> 01:10:29.017
You're right! You're right!

01:10:36.650 --> 01:10:39.402
What are you doing?

01:10:40.278 --> 01:10:41.529
Denji!

01:10:42.155 --> 01:10:44.615
There you are, Chainsaw!

01:10:44.616 --> 01:10:48.244
Denji! I'm going to make you
regret coming back to life!

01:10:49.579 --> 01:10:53.791
Beam! Don't make me regret this!

01:10:53.792 --> 01:10:55.085
Okay!

01:10:57.295 --> 01:10:59.214
Damn! Those guys...

01:10:59.798 --> 01:11:01.215
It's a monster battle!

01:11:01.216 --> 01:11:04.094
We're just going to
have to sit it out and watch.

01:11:17.065 --> 01:11:20.067
You keep missing!

01:11:20.068 --> 01:11:21.860
You're like a cockroach.

01:11:21.861 --> 01:11:25.072
I'm tired of the explosions!

01:11:25.073 --> 01:11:27.367
Chainsaw!

01:11:38.086 --> 01:11:40.171
- Take that!
- Ouch!

01:11:42.215 --> 01:11:44.508
What a waste.

01:11:44.509 --> 01:11:47.177
I cut off a beautiful woman's leg.

01:11:47.178 --> 01:11:50.473
Lady Reze! Take my blood!

01:11:55.979 --> 01:11:57.896
Oh! Good!

01:11:57.897 --> 01:11:59.357
Wait, that's not good!

01:11:59.858 --> 01:12:02.902
This is crazy.

01:12:04.612 --> 01:12:05.613
Oh!

01:12:13.496 --> 01:12:15.040
Grab on to something!

01:12:15.790 --> 01:12:18.168
I can't! I can't!

01:12:27.385 --> 01:12:28.386
It's okay.

01:12:29.971 --> 01:12:32.890
It's okay! You can let go!

01:12:32.891 --> 01:12:36.895
If I'm going to die, I don't care!
It just means today was my day to die.

01:12:37.479 --> 01:12:38.897
I'll be fine.

01:12:39.606 --> 01:12:42.149
I've been ready to die for a long time.

01:13:09.385 --> 01:13:11.428
Why?

01:13:11.429 --> 01:13:13.388
Why did you touch my hand?

01:13:13.389 --> 01:13:16.226
- Do you want to die?
- Of course I don't want to die!

01:13:20.772 --> 01:13:23.691
How much did my lifespan
decrease just now?

01:13:27.278 --> 01:13:28.404
About two months.

01:13:35.703 --> 01:13:38.957
If you want to die,
then die somewhere far away from me.

01:13:39.999 --> 01:13:42.043
I can't take it anymore,
watching someone die

01:13:42.752 --> 01:13:44.379
right in front of me.

01:14:05.441 --> 01:14:07.902
Lord Chainsaw!
We're in trouble! Something's coming!

01:14:08.570 --> 01:14:10.488
Lord Chainsaw--

01:14:15.285 --> 01:14:17.120
Hmm? Huh?

01:14:39.893 --> 01:14:42.770
Lord Chainsaw!

01:15:46.251 --> 01:15:47.752
Whoa.

01:15:56.010 --> 01:15:57.929
You were hanging in there
for a pretty long time.

01:15:59.597 --> 01:16:00.807
But I think it's time now...

01:16:03.434 --> 01:16:04.936
to put an end to this.

01:16:16.239 --> 01:16:18.199
That was close!

01:16:19.367 --> 01:16:20.492
Beam!

01:16:20.493 --> 01:16:23.997
Lord Chainsaw!
I'll make sure you won't regret this!

01:16:34.549 --> 01:16:36.258
Hey! This is bad!

01:16:36.259 --> 01:16:38.719
He's going to turn the whole city
into mincemeat at this rate!

01:16:38.720 --> 01:16:42.556
Beam! We've got to get
that fat-ass to shut up first!

01:16:42.557 --> 01:16:43.725
Okay!

01:16:55.028 --> 01:16:57.030
I found you!

01:17:02.952 --> 01:17:06.539
Die! Chainsaw!

01:17:35.610 --> 01:17:36.778
Yeah!

01:17:37.487 --> 01:17:39.988
Beam! Send me flying!

01:17:39.989 --> 01:17:41.991
Yeah!

01:17:49.499 --> 01:17:52.292
This makes it easy for me!

01:17:52.293 --> 01:17:55.671
All I have to do
is swing my chainsaws around...

01:17:56.255 --> 01:17:59.384
like crazy!

01:18:03.596 --> 01:18:04.764
Whoa!

01:18:06.015 --> 01:18:08.308
Beam!

01:18:08.309 --> 01:18:11.145
Lord Chainsaw!

01:18:29.497 --> 01:18:31.915
Stay away!

01:18:35.628 --> 01:18:37.546
Come on!

01:19:12.665 --> 01:19:14.583
We did it! Beam!

01:19:14.584 --> 01:19:16.210
Where's Reze?

01:19:17.670 --> 01:19:19.338
Ah! Lord Chainsaw!

01:20:17.939 --> 01:20:19.273
Whoa!

01:21:06.028 --> 01:21:07.487
Ouch!

01:21:07.488 --> 01:21:09.114
You saved me, Beam!

01:21:12.243 --> 01:21:15.913
Denji. Don't you think
it's about time you gave up?

01:21:16.539 --> 01:21:17.873
Uh...

01:21:18.666 --> 01:21:19.667
No.

01:21:40.271 --> 01:21:44.191
You're being a huge pain in the ass.
Just hurry up and die already.

01:21:44.817 --> 01:21:50.072
Then you should have just
killed me when we first met!

01:21:52.199 --> 01:21:53.701
There's nowhere left to run.

01:21:54.452 --> 01:21:55.703
I wouldn't be so sure about that.

01:21:56.329 --> 01:21:59.914
You shouldn't have taught me how to swim.

01:21:59.915 --> 01:22:02.668
Huh... You're going to swim?

01:22:32.031 --> 01:22:33.449
Chains?

01:22:52.802 --> 01:22:56.931
Can you still explode when you're wet?

01:24:44.955 --> 01:24:46.415
I can't believe it.

01:24:47.458 --> 01:24:49.877
Why did you resurrect me?

01:24:52.254 --> 01:24:55.007
I have a great life.

01:24:55.674 --> 01:24:59.677
No matter how many times
I get beat up or die,

01:24:59.678 --> 01:25:03.349
as long as I get to eat good food
the next day, I can forgive.

01:25:04.725 --> 01:25:05.726
But...

01:25:07.186 --> 01:25:10.147
if I capture you and hand you over
to Public Safety,

01:25:10.731 --> 01:25:14.652
I'd feel like I had a fish bone
stuck in my throat.

01:25:18.823 --> 01:25:21.449
Even if I were living
a good life every day,

01:25:21.450 --> 01:25:24.829
it would feel bad, having something
poking the back of my throat.

01:25:30.251 --> 01:25:33.753
Do you think you would
still say that if I killed you right now?

01:25:35.631 --> 01:25:37.632
If someone's going to kill me,

01:25:37.633 --> 01:25:39.260
then I'd rather be killed
by a beautiful woman.

01:25:50.354 --> 01:25:51.564
Ah...

01:25:53.148 --> 01:25:58.237
Do you really still believe
that I like you for real?

01:25:59.363 --> 01:26:03.742
The look on my face when I met you,
and the way I blushed... It was all a lie.

01:26:04.660 --> 01:26:06.661
I just trained myself how to do it.

01:26:08.038 --> 01:26:10.207
I failed.

01:26:10.749 --> 01:26:13.502
I took too much time before I fought you.

01:26:15.129 --> 01:26:17.464
I'm going to run away now.

01:26:24.221 --> 01:26:25.806
Do you want to run away together?

01:26:27.266 --> 01:26:28.350
Huh?

01:26:29.143 --> 01:26:32.187
I can fight too.
You'll have a better chance at escaping.

01:26:34.231 --> 01:26:36.983
I killed lots of people.

01:26:36.984 --> 01:26:41.947
If you let me get away,
that would make you complicit in murder.

01:26:42.448 --> 01:26:43.991
Do you understand what that means?

01:26:45.200 --> 01:26:46.201
Uh...

01:26:46.785 --> 01:26:49.121
I know I shouldn't,
but I've got no choice.

01:26:49.622 --> 01:26:51.165
I still like you.

01:26:52.291 --> 01:26:54.125
You said it was all a lie.

01:26:54.126 --> 01:26:57.212
But you did teach me how to swim. Right?

01:27:39.421 --> 01:27:40.630
Hey!

01:27:40.631 --> 01:27:43.591
You should learn to be smarter.

01:27:43.592 --> 01:27:46.261
Reze! Hey, Reze!

01:27:51.850 --> 01:27:56.354
I'm going to be waiting
at the café at lunch!

01:27:56.355 --> 01:27:58.065
You'd better--

01:28:02.194 --> 01:28:05.114
Get up, Beam! My hand won't move!

01:28:06.281 --> 01:28:08.033
Rev up my engine!

01:28:52.578 --> 01:28:55.955
<i>There's a fairy tale
that mothers in the Soviet Union tell</i>

01:28:55.956 --> 01:28:57.041
<i>when scolding their children.</i>

01:28:58.167 --> 01:29:04.547
<i>The story says that there's a secret room
in the military's munitions storehouse.</i>

01:29:04.548 --> 01:29:06.550
And the secret room is filled
with orphans.

01:29:09.762 --> 01:29:12.263
The kids who live there
don't have any freedom.

01:29:12.264 --> 01:29:13.891
They're not allowed to go outside.

01:29:14.892 --> 01:29:16.434
They're treated like objects.

01:29:16.435 --> 01:29:19.438
And the military uses their bodies
for experiments until they die.

01:29:20.022 --> 01:29:22.566
It was supposed to be just a fairy tale.

01:29:23.067 --> 01:29:27.279
But one day, a newspaper reported that
that secret room really did exist.

01:29:28.155 --> 01:29:30.198
<i>An American journalist was the one
who uncovered the story.</i>

01:29:30.199 --> 01:29:32.159
<i>It was all over the news.</i>

01:29:32.659 --> 01:29:36.121
<i>They published photos
of the children who were there.</i>

01:29:36.622 --> 01:29:38.415
<i>But the story soon disappeared.</i>

01:29:38.999 --> 01:29:42.168
<i>The girl who lured Denji in
was one of the kids from that room.</i>

01:29:42.169 --> 01:29:43.294
TYPHOON DEVIL DAMAGE RELIEF FUND

01:29:43.295 --> 01:29:44.838
YOUR SUPPORT AND COOPERATION
ARE APPRECIATED

01:29:45.923 --> 01:29:49.593
A fighter created by the Soviet Union
to serve their country.

01:29:53.430 --> 01:29:56.934
<i>They're called guinea pigs.</i>

01:29:59.895 --> 01:30:04.316
<i>The Yamabiko train bound for
Sendai will soon depart from Platform 12.</i>

01:30:05.109 --> 01:30:07.110
<i>The next stop will be Ueno.</i>

01:30:07.111 --> 01:30:08.486
<i>The train will now depart.</i>

01:30:08.487 --> 01:30:10.738
<i>This is the Yamabiko train
bound for Sendai.</i>

01:30:10.739 --> 01:30:13.366
<i>The train will now depart.
Doors are closing.</i>

01:30:13.367 --> 01:30:15.452
<i>Please stand clear of the closing doors.</i>

01:31:28.150 --> 01:31:29.151
Me too.

01:31:31.862 --> 01:31:34.364
I like the country mouse too.

01:31:36.909 --> 01:31:40.287
One of my friends has a field
in the countryside.

01:31:41.163 --> 01:31:45.000
I go there to help out my friend
every year in the fall.

01:31:46.293 --> 01:31:51.006
The field has mice hiding in the soil
that damage the crops.

01:31:51.924 --> 01:31:56.053
We have to exterminate the mice
before the fields get covered in snow.

01:31:56.637 --> 01:32:02.100
So we dig up the fields and have the dogs
kill the mice hiding inside.

01:32:03.310 --> 01:32:04.519
I wonder why...

01:32:05.354 --> 01:32:06.939
whenever I watch...

01:32:08.357 --> 01:32:09.858
I feel so comforted.

01:32:15.322 --> 01:32:17.449
That's why I like the country mouse.

01:32:53.235 --> 01:32:54.319
<i>Why...</i>

01:32:55.362 --> 01:32:58.824
<i>I wonder why I didn't kill you
the first time we met.</i>

01:33:00.158 --> 01:33:03.203
<i>Denji, to be honest...</i>

01:33:04.955 --> 01:33:08.041
<i>I've never been to school either.</i>

01:33:21.179 --> 01:33:24.266
I told you to come with Hayakawa.

01:33:24.766 --> 01:33:28.353
You didn't want to make
Hayakawa kill a girl.

01:33:29.313 --> 01:33:30.522
You're so kind.

01:33:31.523 --> 01:33:33.900
It's because I'm an angel.

01:33:45.120 --> 01:33:46.121
Hey.

01:33:47.039 --> 01:33:48.707
Is the city a good place?

01:37:56.371 --> 01:37:59.416
Denji. I've got to close the café now.

01:38:01.001 --> 01:38:02.836
That girl was too cute.

01:38:03.503 --> 01:38:05.380
She was from a different world.

01:38:07.173 --> 01:38:10.969
I'm sure you'll meet a girl
who's perfect for you someday.

01:38:22.022 --> 01:38:23.690
RECOMMENDATIONS

01:38:37.537 --> 01:38:40.205
P-P-P-Power!

01:38:41.708 --> 01:38:47.129
I'm back! I tracked you down
by following your scent.

01:38:47.130 --> 01:38:49.716
What a tiny café!

01:38:56.890 --> 01:38:58.390
Hmm?

01:38:58.391 --> 01:39:01.101
Oh. What are you doing with those flowers?

01:39:01.102 --> 01:39:04.689
They would really suit me!
Give them to me!

01:39:19.204 --> 01:39:23.540
Hey! Don't eat them!
They're mine! You thief!

01:39:23.541 --> 01:39:25.584
You idiot!

01:39:25.585 --> 01:39:27.379
Spit them out right now!

01:39:27.879 --> 01:39:31.715
Spit them out! Spit them out!
